                            GrammarTopicId = 41,
                            Description = "",
                            Explanation = "<div>\r\n  <h4>Understanding Future Perfect Tense</h4>\r\n  <p>The Future Perfect Tense is a verb form used to describe actions that will have been completed by a specific point in the future. It gives a sense of completion of a future action and is often used with time expressions.</p>\r\n\r\n  <h4>Forming the Future Perfect Tense</h4>\r\n  <p>To form sentences in the Future Perfect Tense, use the formula:</p>\r\n  <div><b>Subject + will have + past participle of the verb</b></div>\r\n\r\n  <h4>Examples:</h4>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>By next month, I <b>will have finished</b> the project.</li>\r\n    <li>She <b>will have left</b> by the time you get there.</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n\r\n  <h4>Key Time Expressions</h4>\r\n  <p>Time expressions are often used with the Future Perfect Tense to specify when the action will be completed. Common expressions include: <i>by the time, by tomorrow, by next week, by [specific time in the future]</i>, and so forth.</p>\r\n\r\n  <h4>Negative Sentences</h4>\r\n  <p>To make a negative sentence in the Future Perfect Tense, place <b>not</b> between <b>will</b> and <b>have</b>. For example:</p>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>They <b>will not have arrived</b> before the party starts.</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n\r\n  <h4>Interrogative Sentences</h4>\r\n  <p>To form a question in the Future Perfect Tense, invert the subject and <b>will</b>. For example:</p>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li><b>Will</b> you <b>have finished</b> your homework by 8 PM?</li>\r\n  </ul> \r\n\r\n  <h4>Usage</h4>\r\n  <p>This tense is particularly useful for expressing actions that are expected or planned to be completed before a certain future moment. It is helpful in making predictions, setting goals or deadlines, and creating schedules or plans that extend into the future.</p>\r\n\r\n  <h4>Practice Exercise</h4>\r\n  <p>Try to create sentences using the Future Perfect Tense with the following prompts:</p>\r\n  <ul>\r\n    <li>By 2025, I _______ (travel) to Mars.</li>\r\n    <li>She _______ (learn) three languages by the end of the year.</li>\r\n    <li>How many books _______ you _______ (read) by next month?</li>\r\n  </ul>\r\n</div>",
